Package main

Contains all the classes for the CIS 350 Ant Farm Project.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Ant
    Establishes the minimum functionality for all Ants, including WorkingAnts, DiggingAnts, Kings, and Queens.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AntFarm
    This class creates and manages an array of Tiles which are interpreted by the WorldPane and WorldMenuBar classes to create the visible gui.
    AntGui
    This class combines the WorldPane and WorldMenuBar classes into an observable gui.
    Behavior
    This class handles the movements and behaviors of each different Ant Type.
    DiggingAnt
    The DiggingAnt costs 2 food to purchase and can move diagonally up-left, up-right, down-left, and down-right.
    King
    The King costs 10 food to purchase and can move in one space in any direction, diagonally or straight.
    Queen
    Every simulation begins with one Queen ant, and no more can be bought.
    WorkingAnt
    The WorkingAnt costs 5 food to purchase and can move up, down, left, and right.
    WorldMenuBar
    This class creates a menu bar that contains several buttons that can influence the antfarm simulation depicted via WorldPane.
    WorldPane
    This class creates and updates an array of multi-colored labels by analyzing the Tile array from an AntFarm object.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Tile
    This enum represents the different tiles that will need to be displayed by the AntFarm gui.
